Ipsos predicts the ANC will win more than 60 percent of the national vote. While the DA will remain the main opposition but will decline from the 22 percent it achieved in 2014. Ipsos Director, Mari Harris with more on this. Courtesy #DStv403 PRETORIA - Market research and a consulting firm Ipsos predict the ANC will win more than 60 percent of the national vote. The governing party is predicted to receive between 61% and 65%  of the vote. READ: Polls put ANC in front in 2019 Elections While the DA will remain the main opposition but will decline from the 22 percent it achieved in 2014. Ipsos Director, Mari Harris says DA is bound to lose numbers because their supporters have questioned the party’s leadership. However, Harris doesn’t think the DA will lose the Western Cape province.